external_knowledge:
- "master architect" refers to the commissioner;
- "opulent league empire" refers to the leagues with the highest total prize pool;
- "total prize pool" is the sum of prize money across all leagues managed by a commissioner.

- "Top 10 teams" refers to the teams with the highest points difference;
- "Gap" refers to the difference between total points and average points per game;
- "Average length of addresses" is the mean length of the addresses of the users.

sql:
SELECT MAX(avg_points) AS max_average_points
FROM (
  SELECT AVG(points) AS avg_points
  FROM player_stats
  GROUP BY league_id
);

SELECT league_name, prize_pool
FROM leagues
ORDER BY prize_pool DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "average points per league" refers to the total points scored by a player divided by the number of distinct leagues they have played in;
- "high average points per league" implies a significant performance metric, indicating players who consistently score well;
- "more than one league" means the player has participated in at least two different leagues.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the leagues that are performing exceptionally well;
- 'Player performance' is measured by the average points scored by players;
- 'Team strength' is indicated by the number of teams in the league.
